# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dossier — .gitignore (public repo)
#
# Two jobs (per ADR-001):
#   1. Keep personal data and secrets out of public history.
#   2. Keep environment/build noise out of the repo.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Secrets & personal data (ADR-001, defense layer 1) ───────
# Never commit real config or any personal data into the public repo.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.local

# Any locally-present personal data directories.
# (Real data lives in the separate private `dossier-data` repo,
#  but guard against accidental copies landing here.)
data/
output/
generated/
*.docx
*.pdf
!docs/**/*.pdf
cv_*.md
cover_*.md

# Local application database, if one ends up here during dev.
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db

# ── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
*.egg

# Test / coverage / type-check caches
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── uv / virtual environment ─────────────────────────────────
# The virtual environment itself is never committed — it is
# rebuilt from pyproject.toml + uv.lock on any machine.
.venv/
venv/
# Note: uv.lock IS committed (it pins exact dependency versions).
# It is intentionally NOT ignored here.

# ── Editors / IDE ────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# ── macOS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride